    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-10-05T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-10-05T16:00:00-05:00" n="665"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d665">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">340.1115a/129: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kennedy</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="42" xml:id="d665fn42">The same telegram was sent on October
                        5 to the Ambassador in France as No. 1166, and to the Minister in Ireland as
                        No. 33.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-10-05T16:00:00-05:00"
                            >October 5, 1939—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1164. The Government has decided that the repatriation problem has been solved to
                    the point where the use of the five specially diverted ships is no longer
                    necessary for that purpose. Two have already been released to their owners and
                    the <hi rend="italic">Iroquois, St. John</hi> and <hi rend="italic">Acadia</hi>
                    will be released upon their return to the United States. The regular passenger
                    liners in the North Atlantic service will continue to make a turn-around as
                    quickly as possible and will be available for the carriage of passengers to the
                    United States from English, French and Irish ports.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
